<p>Requirement is first,second,third,forth,fifth this work fine when I use string but it doesn't works when I use foreach</p>  <pre><code> List&lt;string&gt; stringList = new List&lt;string&gt;();         stringList.Add("first");         stringList.Add("second");         stringList.Add("third");         stringList.Add("fourth");         stringList.Add("fifth");       string result = string.Join(", ", stringList).TrimEnd(',', ' ');         Console.WriteLine(result);      foreach (var item in stringList)         {             string resultt = string.Join(", ", item).TrimEnd(',', ' ');             Console.WriteLine(resultt);         } </code></pre>  <p>I have to remove comma from last word from a List of string using foreach.</p>